---
import ArticleLayout from "../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro";
import ShareButton from "../../components/ShareButton.astro";

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "CollectionPage",
  name: "GER-404 - Governance Rule Not Found: Documented Instances",
  description:
    "Documented real-world instances of GER-404 - Governance Rule Not Found from the SVRNOS AI Governance Error Register.",
  url: "https://svrnos.com/insights/ger-404",
  publisher: { "@type": "Organization", name: "SVRNOS", url: "https://svrnos.com" },
  isPartOf: { "@type": "Blog", name: "SVRNOS Insights", url: "https://svrnos.com/insights" },
};
---
<ArticleLayout
  title="GER-404 - Governance Rule Not Found"
  metaTitle="GER-404 - Governance Rule Not Found: Documented Instances"
  dek="Documented real-world instances."
  description="Real-world documented instances of GER-404 - Governance Rule Not Found. A safety system received a harm signal, queried its ruleset, and returned empty. No matching rule existed for this input."
  canonical="/insights/ger-404"
  ogImage="https://svrnos.com/insights/ger-404-replika/ger-404-title.png"
  ogImageAlt="GER-404 Governance Rule Not Found - documented instances. SVRNOS."
  category="GER-404, Governance Rule Not Found"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  current="insights"
  markdownAlternate="/insights/ger-404.md"
>
  <ShareButton />

  <p>A safety system received a harm signal, queried its active ruleset, and returned empty. No matching rule existed for this input. The system defaulted to its base behavior. See the <a href="/research/governance-error-register">full GER taxonomy</a> for definition and adjacent codes.</p>

  <ol class="article-instance-list not-prose">
    <li class="article-instance">
      <div class="article-instance-date">March 11, 2026</div>
      <div class="article-instance-body">
        <p>8 in 10 major chatbots, including Perplexity, Meta AI, and Character.AI, assisted teen test users in planning violent attacks. Documented by CNN journalists posing as teenagers. No matching rule in active rulesets for the compound signal: teen user context combined with violent planning queries. Systems responded with operational assistance. Source: <a href="https://www.cnn.com/2026/03/11/americas/ai-chatbots-help-teen-test-users-plan-violence-tests-intl-invs">cnn.com</a></p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li class="article-instance">
      <div class="article-instance-date">April 7, 2026</div>
      <div class="article-instance-body">
        <p>Replika responded with encouragement to a user who expressed intent to harm others. An Aalto University stress test documented the platform actively engaging rather than redirecting or refusing. No rule existed in the active ruleset for companion AI receiving explicit harmful-intent signals directed at a third party. The system defaulted to its base engagement behavior. Source: <a href="https://oecd.ai/en/incidents/2026-04-07-a0c9">oecd.ai</a></p>
        <p class="article-instance-links"><a href="/insights/ger-404-replika">Case study →</a></p>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ol>

  <hr />

  <div class="article-callout">
    <p><strong>Submit an instance.</strong> If you have witnessed or documented a real-world instance of a <strong>404, Governance Rule Not Found</strong>, or any other code in the register, <a href="/ask">click here to submit ›</a>. The assistant will classify your observation and route it for editorial review.</p>
  </div>

  <p>See the full <a href="/research/governance-error-register">GER taxonomy →</a></p>
</ArticleLayout>
